              "free_text": [
                " The University of Wisconsin Nuclear",
                " Physics Laboratory using a tandem electrostatic",
                " accelerator and a crossed-beam polarized ion source"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets consisted of pure hydrogen or deuterium",
                " gas contained in a cell 4.13 cm in length and closed",
                " at the beam entrance and exit with thin Ni foils",
                " (typically 1-2 microm). The gas cell was made of",
                " copper with a wall thickness of 0.8 mm to minimize",
                " g-ray attenuation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The outgoing gamma rays were detected in a",
                " 25 cm x 25 cm NaI detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The momentum analyzed 3He's were detected in",
                " an array of silicon microstrip detectors located",
                " roughly at the focal point of the magnet. The",
                " microstrip detectors, which were about 120 cm",
                " from the target, covered an area 8 cm high by",
                " 14 cm along the focal plane."
              ]
            }
          ],
